        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 1:15PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 115 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Brevard, or 4 miles northeast of Graveyard Fields.
This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mills River, Graveyard Fields, Bent Creek, Cruso, B.R. Parkway-Mount
Pisgah To The Nc Arboretum, Asheville Airport, Looking Glass, Avery
Creek, Forge Mountain, and Mount Pisgah.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
